                        <summary><p>#141. a) Tiruvaiyāṟu, Tiruvaiyāṟu taluk, Tanjavur district, Pañcanātīśvara temple; b) on the western façade of the sanctuary; c) I could not access the inscription because, since a few years, the western and northern façades of the sanctuary are closed to the public (the hair of Śiva are said to have fallen on this side); d) ARE 1894, no. 224; SII 5, no. 523; e) 10th regnal year of Kōrājakesarivarman; f) king difficult to identify; g) inscription not read with anyone; h) because I could neither access nor photograph the inscription, I have provided here the edition established in SII, but without the supply of the missing letters.</p>
                            
